  schema:name "Philosophy of Environment: From Aristotle's Place to Relational Ontologies" ;
  schema:description "A philosophical survey of environment — what surrounds a thing, how boundaries are drawn, and how organisms and their worlds co-constitute each other. From Aristotle's topos through Gibson's affordances, Whitehead's prehensions, and Indigenous relational ontologies." ;
